    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-07-31T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-07-31T11:00:00-05:00" n="544"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d544">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.4016/2130: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-07-31T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 31, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 31—12:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>717. Department’s 330, July 29, 2 p.m.<note n="61" xml:id="d544fn61">Not
                        printed.</note> Regulations imposing restrictions upon Jews visiting health
                    and bathing resorts having been published in the <hi rend="italic">Reich
                        Ministerial Blatt</hi>, note was presented today at the Foreign Office.
                    Opinion was expressed by Foreign Office spokesman regulations would not affect
                    Americans of Jewish faith who desired to visit German spas as such interference
                    was not the intent of the law. No actual cases of interference have been
                    reported.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
